<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Nineteenth session</b> 
Agenda item 3 
<b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil, 
political, economic, social and cultural rights, 
including the right to development 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Report of the Working Group on Enforced or Involuntary 
Disappearances 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Addendum 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Mission to Mexico</b>* 
</p>
<p> <i>Summary</i> 
 At the invitation of the Government, the Working Group on Enforced or Involuntary 
Disappearances visited Mexico from 18 to 31 March 2011. The purpose of the visit was to 
learn about the efforts made by Mexico to deal with enforced disappearances, to assess the 
progress of investigations and the measures adopted to prevent and eradicate 
disappearances and to their combat impunity, as well as to consider matters relating to 
truth, justice and reparation. 
 The Working Group acknowledges the various efforts that Mexico has made in the 
field of human rights, including to combat enforced disappearances, and the challenges 
posed by the current complex public security situation in the context of the fight against 
organized crime. However, Mexico must continue its efforts to ensure observance of the 
rights to the truth, justice and reparation for the victims of enforced disappearance. 
 The Working Group makes a number of recommendations relating to prevention, 
investigations, penalties and reparation for the victims of enforced disappearances, as well 
as on the protection of particularly vulnerable groups. Recommendations worthy of note 
include: to ensure that enforced disappearance is classified as an offence in the criminal 
codes of all the federal entities and that the definition of enforced disappearance in criminal 
legislation is brought into line with that of relevant international instruments; to ensure 
coordination among the public security authorities with a view to the prevention and proper 
</p>
<p>  
</p>
<p> * The summary is being circulated in all official languages. The report proper, which is annexed to the 
summary, is being circulated in the language of submission only and in English. 
</p>
<p> United Nations A/HRC/19/58/Add.2
</p>
